President Trump delivered remarks at the U.S. Capitol to honor the life of Billy Graham. He highlighted Graham's impact as a preacher and evangelist, both in the United States and around the world. Trump emphasized Graham's message of God's love and his dedication to reaching out to the neglected and downtrodden. He also noted the importance of prayer in American history and the role of faith in sustaining the nation. Trump concluded by expressing gratitude for Graham's life and praying for more individuals like him to spread a message of love and hope.